The cosmetologist board shall issue an apprentice cosmetologist license to any person who:
Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
Is at least sixteen (16) years of age;
Has a high school diploma, General Educational Development (GED) diploma, or the results from the Test for Adult Basic Education indicating a score equivalent to the twelfth grade of high school;
Has official certification from the state board or agency that certifies cosmetology schools that the applicant has graduated from a licensed school of cosmetology requiring one thousand eight hundred (1,800) hours within ten (10) years of submitting an application for licensure;
Has passed an examination prescribed by the board to determine fitness to practice as an apprentice cosmetologist; and
Has paid a fee of twenty-five dollars ($25).

The cosmetologist board shall issue a cosmetologist license to any person who:
Has a high school diploma, General Educational Development (GED) diploma, or the results from the Test for Adult Basic Education indicating a score equivalent to the twelfth grade of high school;
Has practiced as a licensed cosmetology apprentice for at least six (6) months under the immediate supervision of a licensed cosmetologist;
Has satisfactorily passed an examination prescribed by the board to determine fitness to practice cosmetology; and
Has paid a fee of twenty-five dollars ($25).

The cosmetologist board shall issue a license to act as a nail technician to any person who:
Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
Has official certification from the state board or agency that certifies cosmetology schools that the applicant has completed satisfactorily a nail technician course of study of six hundred (600) hours in a licensed school of cosmetology within ten (10) years of submitting an application for licensure;
Has satisfactorily passed an examination prescribed by the board to determine fitness to practice as a nail technician;
Has a high school diploma, General Educational Development (GED) diploma, or the results from the Test for Adult Basic Education indicating a score equivalent to the twelfth grade of high school; and
Has paid a fee of twenty-five dollars ($25).

The cosmetologist board shall issue a license to teach cosmetology to any person who:
Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
Has a high school diploma, General Educational Development (GED) diploma, or the results from the Test for Adult Basic Education indicating a score equivalent to the twelfth grade of high school;
Has held an apprentice instructor license for at least six (6) months;
Has satisfactorily passed the examination for the teaching of cosmetology as prescribed by the board; and
Has paid a fee of fifty dollars ($50).

The cosmetologist board may issue a license to operate a school of cosmetology to any person who:
Has complied with the administrative regulations promulgated by the board including but not limited to administrative regulations governing the necessary equipment, supplies, and facilities;
Has furnished proof to the board that the school of cosmetology is needed, that he or she is otherwise qualified to operate a school of cosmetology, and that he or she intends to establish a bona fide school for the education and training of competent cosmetologists and that he or she will employ a sufficient number of licensed instructors of cosmetology to conduct the school;
Has as manager at all times a person who is:
Licensed as an instructor;
Charged with the responsibility of ensuring that all applicable statutes and administrative regulations are complied with; and
Responsible for having a sufficient number of licensed instructors of cosmetology to conduct the school. The designated manager shall be approved by the board before a license may be issued;
Complies with the administrative regulations promulgated by the board including but not limited to those regarding courses, curriculum, and hours of instruction;
Otherwise complies with this chapter;
Has paid a fee of one thousand five hundred dollars ($1,500);
Has been a resident of Kentucky for five (5) years, if the applicant is an individual. If the applicant is a firm or corporation, it shall be a Kentucky corporation or licensed or qualified to do business in Kentucky and shall have been in existence for a period of at least five (5) years;
Any student enrolling in the school shall pay a fee of fifteen dollars ($15) to the board before enrollment in the school shall be allowed; and
The transfer of any license to operate a school of cosmetology shall require the board's approval and shall become effective upon filing a new application with the board and paying a fee of one thousand five hundred dollars ($1,500).

The annual renewal license or permit fee for each type of license or permit renewal shall be as follows:
Apprentice cosmetologist -- $20;
Cosmetologist -- $20;
Nail technician -- $20;
Beauty salon -- $25;
Nail salon -- $25;
Apprentice instructor of cosmetology -- $25;
Instructor of cosmetology -- $35;
Cosmetology school -- $150;
Threading permit -- $20; and
Threading facility permit -- $25.

Applications for examinations required by this section shall be accompanied by an examination fee as follows:
Apprentice cosmetologist -- $75;
Cosmetologist -- $75;
Nail technician -- $75;
Instructor of cosmetology -- $100;
Cosmetologist out-of-state -- $120; and
Instructor out-of-state -- $200.

The fee for the restoration of an expired license where the period of expiration does not exceed five (5) years from date of expiration, shall be as follows:
Apprentice cosmetologist -- $75;
Cosmetologist -- $75;
Nail technician -- $75;
Beauty salon -- $75;
Nail salon -- $75;
Cosmetology school -- $750;
Instructor -- $100; and
Apprentice instructor -- $75.

The requirements for a new license for any person whose license has expired for a period exceeding five (5) years shall be as follows:
Cosmetologists shall retake and pass the practical examination only;
Apprentice cosmetologists shall complete four hundred fifty (450) additional hours training in a licensed school of cosmetology and pass all the prescribed examinations;
Instructors of cosmetology shall retake and pass both the practical and theory examination;
Nail technicians shall retake and pass the practical and theory examination; and
The appropriate restoration fee as set forth in subsection (11) of this section shall be required.
